{
  "version": "0.4",
  "title": "About – Pillars & Credentials",
  "type": "page",
  "content": [
    {
      "id": "about_approach",
      "elType": "section",
      "settings": {
        "layout": "full_width",
        "_title": "Approach - 3 Pillars"
      },
      "elements": [
        {
          "id": "approach_col1",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {},
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "approach_1_heading",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Intent Over Instinct",
                "header_size": "h3",
                "align": "center"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "approach_1_text",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>Every image I make is deliberate. I don't walk into a shoot hoping good moments happen. I prepare for them. The brief, the location, the light, the sequence of the day, all of it considered so that when the real moments arrive, I'm already in exactly the right place to catch them.</p>"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "approach_col2",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {},
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "approach_2_heading",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Understand Before You Create",
                "header_size": "h3",
                "align": "center"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "approach_2_text",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>I spend more time in conversation before a shoot than most photographers spend on the entire session. Who are you? Who are you speaking to? What do they care about? What makes them trust someone? The image that resonates with a London agency is a different thing entirely to the one that resonates with an independent Brighton founder, and knowing which you need changes everything.</p>"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "approach_col3",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {},
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "approach_3_heading",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Personality Over Perfection",
                "header_size": "h3",
                "align": "center"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "approach_3_text",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>A technically flawless image that misses who you actually are is worthless. The image that's slightly imperfect but makes you feel unmistakably like yourself, and makes your ideal client think <em>that's exactly who I want to work with</em>. That's the one we're making. Every time. That's the only measure that matters.</p>"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "about-credentials",
      "elType": "section",
      "settings": {
        "_title": "Credentials & Proof",
        "layout": "boxed"
      },
      "elements": [
        {
          "id": "cred-intro-col",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 100,
            "text_align": "center"
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "cred-intro-heading",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Work That Speaks for Itself",
                "header_size": "h2",
                "align": "center"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "cred-col-1",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 25,
            "_column_size_tablet": 50,
            "_column_size_mobile": 100,
            "text_align": "center"
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "cred-heading-1",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Gallery Exhibition",
                "header_size": "h4",
                "align": "center"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "cred-text-1",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>The Brighton Spirit Collection, exhibited at the bar of the Hotel du Vin Brighton, one of the city’s most celebrated luxury venues.</p>"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "cred-col-2",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 25,
            "_column_size_tablet": 50,
            "_column_size_mobile": 100,
            "text_align": "center"
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "cred-heading-2",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Music Photography",
                "header_size": "h4",
                "align": "center"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "cred-text-2",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>From open mic nights to headline acts, with pit access for artists including Skunk Anansie, the Beach Boys, and Gomez at The Concorde 2, Brighton. No flash, no control, three songs. Pure craft.</p>"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "cred-col-3",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 25,
            "_column_size_tablet": 50,
            "_column_size_mobile": 100,
            "text_align": "center"
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "cred-heading-3",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Community Documentary",
                "header_size": "h4",
                "align": "center"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "cred-text-3",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>Organisations including Slack City invest in having their live events documented, for posterity, prosperity, and presence. Real stories, told with clarity and intent.</p>"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "cred-col-4",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 25,
            "_column_size_tablet": 50,
            "_column_size_mobile": 100,
            "text_align": "center"
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "cred-heading-4",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "A Decade of Visual Work",
                "header_size": "h4",
                "align": "center"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "cred-text-4",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p>The City Spirit series began in 2016. What started on Millennium Bridge has become a collection spanning iconic locations across the UK and Europe.</p>"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}